@baseURL = http://localhost:3001

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 1. Ejecuta "### Login exitoso" primero
// 2. WebStorm asigna automáticamente {{token}}
// 3. VS Code: copia token a .rest-client.env.json
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Obtener información de la API (público)
GET {{baseURL}}/about

### 2. Login exitoso
POST {{baseURL}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@mail.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("token", response.body.data.token);
%}

### 3. Login: email incorrecto
POST {{baseURL}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "noexiste@mail.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### 4. Login: contraseña incorrecta
POST {{baseURL}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@mail.com",
  "password": "wrongpass"
}

### 5. Login: campos vacíos
POST {{baseURL}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "",
  "password": ""
}